data.enText: to make sth white or pale by a chemical process or by the effect of light from the sun; to become white or pale in this way

data.chText: 他的头发被太阳晒得发白。
data.enText: His hair was bleached by the sun .

data.chText: 她把头发染成了金黄色。
在阳光中变白的动物骸骨
data.enText: bones of animals bleaching in the sun
a chemical that is used to make sth become white or pale and as a disinfectant (= to prevent infection from spreading)

ex.chText: 太阳把蓝色桌布晒掉色了。
ex.enText: The sun faded the blue-coloured tablecloth.

ex.chText: 这个牌子的牛仔裤不会褪色。
ex.enText: This brand of jeans will not fade.

synonyms.bx: 指（使）某物失去颜色和光泽。

ex.chText: 他因常年辛苦工作而白发苍苍。
ex.enText: Years of toil blanched his hair.

ex.chText: 这种材料在阳光照射下会变白。
ex.enText: This material blanches in the sun.

synonyms.bx: 指（使）某人因害怕或震惊而变得面色苍白或（使）某物变白。

ex.chText: 我怎样才能在家美白牙齿呢？
ex.enText: How can I bleach my teeth at home?

ex.chText: 大衣被太阳晒得褪了色。
ex.enText: The coat was bleached by the sun.

synonyms.bx: 指通过日照或使用化学品使某物颜色变淡或变白。

ex.chText: 太阳逐渐把窗帘晒褪色了。
ex.enText: The sun discoloured the curtain day by day.

ex.chText: 这个苹果是昨天切开的，现在已经变色了。
ex.enText: The apple was cut yesterday and it is already discoloured.

synonyms.bx: 指（使）某物变色，通常变得比以前难看。

ex.chText: 比赛结果出来之后，她的脸色明显变白了。
ex.enText: She visibly whitened when the game result was released.

ex.chText: 大雪为整片森林披上了银装。
我怎样才能漂白我的衬衫呢？
ex.enText: How can I whiten my blouse?

synonyms.bx: 指（使）某人的脸色或某物变白或在原来的基础上变得更白。

tr: the act of whitening something by bleaching it (exposing it to sunlight or using a chemical bleaching agent)
the whiteness that results from removing the color from something
example: a complete bleach usually requires several applications

tr: an agent that makes things white or colorless

example: The sun bleached the red shirt

value.def: If you bleach something, you use a chemical to make it white or pale in colour.

example.ex: These products don't bleach the hair.
example.tran: 这些产品不会使头发变白。
市面上的面粉是经过人工漂白的。

value.def: If the sun bleaches something, or something bleaches, its colour gets paler until it is almost white.

example.ex: The tree's  roots are stripped and hung to season and bleach...
example.tran: 树根剥皮后挂起来风干晒白。

example.ex: The sun will bleach the hairs on your face...
example.tran: 太阳会使你脸上的汗毛发白。

example.ex: He has hair which is naturally black but which has been bleached by the sun.
example.tran: 他的头发本来是黑色的，不过被太阳晒白了。

value.def: Bleach is a chemical that is used to make cloth white, or to clean things thoroughly and kill germs.

trans: 含氯漂白剂；漂白水；氯漂；氯漂白；氯漂白剂
